args:
The party arrives at the circus festival and 
accepts a challenge from a rival troupe that
uses fiends in their show. The beasts run
amok during the performance, however,
forcing the party to save the townspeople
from the chaos that ensues.
Looks like that's the last of the fiends.
Then let's make for the town already!
Oh ho! Welcome to the circus festival!\nYou can check in right over there.
Wooo! We made it in time!
This place is really abuzz with activity.
Might we consider taking a little rest?\nComing down from the mountain through\nthe night has me rather exhausted.
Yeah, you have a point. After check in,\nlet's get off our feet for a bit.
...Well, everyone seems settled.\nCan I help with anything, Annelie?
Yep! No better way to draw a crowd.

And each one represents a possible butt
in a seat. Now stop with the questions
and get with the handing-them-out bit,
if you would be so kind!
Ladieeeees and gentlemeeeeen!\nOur circus has just pulled into town,\nand we want to see YOU there!

There's only one tent with an action-packed
dragon tamer show, and that's OURS!
So don't feel averse to reach for the purse,
because tickets are going faaaaast!
Good gravy! It's rainin' flyers out here!
Let's help pass them out if we can.\n...Step right up, folks! Step right up!
Er, please attend our circus if you find\nsuch things pleasing in general...?
The heck was THAT, Elisanne?\nYou can't just whisper a bunch of\nmealy-mouthed nonsense!
I'm still learning this, thank you very mu...\nHuh? Annelie! Behind you!
Good heavens, what utter rot!\nYour friend there is the one who\nplaced herself in MY path!

Oh ho! Why, observing my rival, of course!
I heard you were waylaid by blackguards
on the mountain trail, mmm? Such a thing
must have been so very traumatic.
And yet, here you all are, safe as houses.\nWhy, it's enough to pickle my kippers!
I take it you sent those thieves?
Oh ho! A new recruit with a sharp tongue,\nis it? What a fine addition you will make.

And to think how your participation in this
festival was nearly imperiled by our
poaching of your former troupe members.
My, but this simply IS marvelous.
We got better things to do than listen\nto sarcastic quips, old man. ...Er, Annelie?
It does my heart good to hear you praise\nus like that, Gustav.
Please, you MUST take a flyer!
I've no need of your rubbish,\nyou madwoman!
Your dragon tamer drivel is more\nwashed up than a beached whale!

WE shall be putting on a display of fiend
taming! It's impressive, replete with thrills
aplenty, and MILES apart from any of your
＂dragon＂ business. Harumph!

You are performing with FIENDS?!
I pray you have the manpower to
keep the beasts subdued. Soldiers,
perhaps, or mercenaries if not.
We've no need of such cruel, violent boors\nin OUR troupe, my good woman!
For we are entertainers in the end!
You can't put on a show that might\nexpose your guests to danger!

I know we've had our differences, Gustav,
but I ALSO know you have real talent.
There is no need to rely on cheap fiend
tricks for your performance!
Guests are always looking for evolution.\nThe next big thing. Surely even you must\nbe aware of that little fact, mmm?
Also, we are professionals! If you don't\nbelieve we can keep them wrangled,\ncome feast eyes on our show. Harumph!
What are we gonna do, ma'am?
I don't like this one bit, Fritz.\nWe'd better go take a look.
Welcome, my good and decent friends!\nWelcome to our circus!
Step inside and enjoy our breathtaking\nperformances—including an absolutely\nthrilling display of fiend taming!
Can regular folk really tame fiends?\nHell, can ANYONE?
For their sake, I really hope so.
And now, at long last, our fiend tamer\ntakes to the stage! Be dazzled! \nBe amazed! Be...STUPIFIED!
Uh, guys? Is it just me, or does that fiend\nlook kinda...disinterested?
What's your problem, you stupid fiend?!\nDo this like we practiced!
N-no! Easy there! Bad fiend! Bad!\nAAAUGH! RUN FOR YOUR LIIIIIVES!
I say, how dare you run away and leave\nyour ringmaster all alone! Stoooop!
That two-bit ringmaster blasted outta here\nlike his pants were on fire! What a loser.
What kind of dastard runs off and\nabandons his guests?!
Secure an evacuation route, now!\nWe need to get the guests out of here!
Eeek! There are fiends pouring\nout of that tent!
We need to chase them down. Come on!
Urgh... There's so many of them!\nGetting everyone to safety won't\nbe simple...
No, look! That girl is riding it!
My associate Liger here is going to guide\nyou all to a place of safety.
Fear not! I sit astride him, and guarantee\nyour safety in his most-capable claws!\nCome now! Make haste!
She's talking like she does during a show,\nand it's completely taking away their\napprehensions about Liger!
Liger, you must take care of the people!
Tch! How many fiends did that old geezer\nactually plan to tame?
We keep slaying and slaying,\nbut there's no end in sight!
Wait a second. Maybe their cries are\nactually attracting other nearby fiends!
We'd better come up with a plan before\nthis entire town is overrun!
Bwa ha ha! Didja forget about yer\nnew recruits?!
We love this kinda stuff!\nIt's sorta what we do.

Also, we went to the trouble of learning
how to make our fighting movements
charming for people to watch, so we may
as well take advantage of that training.
We'll be all right if we all fight together.\nNow let's begin our show!
These cats are turning out to be\nsome pretty great colleagues, ma'am.
Let's work together and take these\nfiends out!
We'll use our new skills to protect\nthe village AND its people!
